parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty transmission shifting can cause the vehicle to jerk, lurch, or hesitate, leading to loss of control, accidents, or sudden stops, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or lurches when shifting gears
hesitates to shift
or shifts harshly
causing an uncomfortable ride. The transmission may also make unusual noises
such as whining or grinding sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle can move unexpectedly, even when the transmission is in park, which can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls away or moves on its own
even when the transmission is in park
and the brake pedal is applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or cease running, leading to loss of control, accidents, or sudden stops, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine ceases running
often without warning
and may be accompanied by unusual noises
such as grinding or knocking sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
or the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty steering and suspension can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake excessively, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or shakes excessively
often when stopping or driving on rough roads
and may be accompanied by unusual noises
such as metal knocking sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake assist system can cause the vehicle to experience sudden and unexpected loss of braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses, and putting the driver and passengers at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floorboard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake assist light comes on
the vehicle shakes or makes weird noises when braking
the brakes fail to respond
the vehicle slides or skids when braking.

symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy

the vehicle takes longer to stop

symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floorboard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake assist light comes on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unpredictable brake behavior can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses, and putting the driver and passengers at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floorboard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake assist light comes on
the vehicle shakes or makes weird noises when braking

the vehicle slides or skids when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning Cadillac Cue system can cause distractions while driving, making it difficult to control the vehicle, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The Cadillac Cue screen is stuck on a warning screen
randomly scrolls through screens/selecting features
and fails to switch into camera view mode
making safety cameras inaccessible. The system also turns the AC/heater on and off at random
affects the DVD system
navigation system
and volume levels
and can cause the radio/Bluetooth/DVD system to play at full blast.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning mirrors and running boards can cause distractions while driving, potentially leading to accidents, and can also cause physical harm if the running boards retract or extend unexpectedly.
symptoms: The side view mirrors tilt randomly to the sky or ground
and the saved position is retained. The running boards extend and retract unexpectedly
almost trapping the foot.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Key Fob and Locking System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning key fob and locking system can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to accidents if the mirrors fold in while driving.
symptoms: The key fob can accidentally lock or unlock the vehicle
causing the mirrors to fold in or out while driving. The vehicle may not unlock or start when the push-start button is depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning vehicle control and safety systems can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially put the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or breaks suddenly
making it difficult to control
and the steering and brakes may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Cadillac Cue system can cause a range of safety issues, as it controls many functions of the vehicle, including navigation, communication, and entertainment.
symptoms: The Cadillac Cue system screen freezes or becomes unresponsive
affecting the vehicle's functionality and safety.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The air conditioning condenser leak can cause the system to fail, leading to reduced cooling performance and potential overheating, which can affect vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: The air conditioning system does not cool properly
and refrigerant leaks are detected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unusual noise from the vehicle can be a sign of a underlying mechanical issue, which can affect vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: A loud
unusual noise is heard from the bottom of the vehicle when accelerating
which can be distracting and potentially mask other important sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the autoclose feature can cause the hatchback to close unexpectedly, potentially causing injury or damage.
symptoms: The hatchback closes randomly while loading or unloading
without warning
and does not stop or sense a person's presence.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission issues can cause the vehicle to surge or buck, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or bucks when switching gears
even when at a full stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the OnStar system can cause delayed or failed emergency response, which can have serious consequences in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The OnStar system does not activate in the event of an accident
despite being advertised as a safety feature.
